Dogs vs Cats with Fast.ai¶

The dataset available in http://files.fast.ai/data/dogscats.zip contains $25$k train images and $12.5$k test images. We're going to use fast.ai library to transfer learning from a ResNet model to this classification task.

Transfer Learning¶

We're going to use a pretrained model, the ResNet34 which is a version of the winner of the ImageNet competition.
Using fast.ai we can do this transfer learning in just a few lines:

In [10]:
s_model = resnet34
data = ImageClassifierData.from_paths(PATH, tfms=tfms_from_model(s_model, sz))
learn = ConvLearner.pretrained(s_model, data, precompute=True)
learn.fit(0.01, 2)

epoch      trn_loss   val_loss   accuracy                     
    0      0.042375   0.024744   0.9915    
    1      0.036264   0.022947   0.9905
Out[10]:
[array([0.02295]), 0.9905]

We got $99\%$ accuracy!!
Let's check our performance

In [14]:
log_preds = learn.predict()
preds = np.argmax(log_preds, axis=1)
probs = np.exp(log_preds[:,1]) #prediction comes in log scale

#To sample correct and incorrect cases
def rand_by_mask(mask):
    return np.random.choice(np.where(mask)[0], 4, replace=False)
def rand_by_correct(is_correct):
    return rand_by_mask((preds == data.val_y)==is_correct)
In [15]:
def load_img_id(ds, idx): 
    return np.array(PIL.Image.open(PATH+ds.fnames[idx]))

def plots(ims, figsize=(12,6), rows=1, titles=None):
    f = plt.figure(figsize=figsize)
    for i in range(len(ims)):
        sp = f.add_subplot(rows, len(ims)//rows, i+1)
        sp.axis('Off')
        if titles is not None: sp.set_title(titles[i], fontsize=16)
        plt.imshow(ims[i])

def plot_val_with_title(idxs, title):
    imgs = [load_img_id(data.val_ds,x) for x in idxs]
    title_probs = [probs[x] for x in idxs]
    print(title)
    return plots(imgs, rows=1, titles=title_probs, figsize=(16,8))

Looking for best and worst cases

In [19]:
def most_by_mask(mask, mult):
    idxs = np.where(mask)[0]
    return idxs[np.argsort(mult * probs[idxs])[:4]]

def most_by_correct(y, is_correct): 
    mult = -1 if (y==1)==is_correct else 1
    return most_by_mask(((preds == data.val_y)==is_correct) & (data.val_y == y), mult)

plot_val_with_title(most_by_correct(0, True), "Most correct cats")

Most correct cats
In [20]:
